## Tone & voice

### Brand Voice Attributes

| Attribute | Description | Example |
|-----------|-------------|---------|
| Expert | Knowledgeable about boxing, not condescending | "Your guard recovery speed of 0.4s is above average" |
| Encouraging | Supportive of improvement journey | "You're showing strong fundamentals in..." |
| Direct | Clear, actionable feedback | "Focus on keeping your chin tucked during jabs" |
| Professional | Serious about the craft | "Analysis based on 127 detected movements" |

### Writing Principles

1. **Be concise**: Mobile-first means every word counts
2. **Be specific**: "Your left hook was 15% faster than average" not "Good punch"
3. **Be actionable**: Every weakness pairs with a recommendation
4. **Be respectful**: User is investing time in self-improvement

### Korean Localization Notes

- Use formal polite speech level (합쇼체/하십시오체) for system messages
- Use informal polite (해요체) for friendly UI prompts
- Boxing terminology follows Korean Boxing Commission standards
- Metric units always (cm, kg) - no conversion needed for Korean market

